{
  "texts": [
    "To create training samples, a sliding window approach is used where each window of L time steps is treated as an input sequence, followed by the target values for the next H steps.",
    "Specifically, the window slides one time step forward at each iteration, capturing overlapping sub sequences and allowing the model to learn from multiple segments of historical data.",
    "For example, the first window would cover time steps 1 to L, and the target would be steps L+1 to L+H; the next window would then shift to cover time steps 2 to L+1, with the target now covering steps L+2 to L+H+1, and so on.",
    "This method ensures the model learns temporal patterns effectively by leveraging all possible sequences in the time series.",
    "Each training sample thus consists of past data over L steps across all sensors and the target values for the next H steps."
  ]
}